               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; name of the scribe; directives to the ministers and their abbreviations; titles of the books to be read; ʾǝgäle, qǝbaʾ; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text I is called Mäṣḥafä ṭǝmqät on fol. 1r.</note>
                     <note>- Text I contains an embedded colophon (fol. 25v) which mentions the Coptic, Arabic and Gǝʿǝz languages (but it is unclear, probably corrupted) and possibly the name of the scribe, ʾAṣfä Krǝstos.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
